example.p:
Given y'' -2y'-3y=4e^{-t}, we are led to try y_p=Ae^{-t}: 

	(Ae^{-t}) - 2(-Ae^{-t}) - 3Ae^{-t} \amp = 4e^{-t} 
	 0 \amp 4e^{-t} 
. This is impossible to satisfy. What's happened is that the characteristic polynomial is (s+1)(s-3), so e^{-t} is part of the null solution (as the above calculation verified). Instead we have to use y_p=Ate^{-t}, which gives 

	 Ae^{-t}(t-2) - 2Ae^{-t}(1-t) - 3Ate^{-t} \amp = 4e^{-t} 
	 -4Ae^{-t} \amp 4e^{-t} 
, so A=1 and y_p is valid.

program.input:
%bc = webread('https://api.coindesk.com/v1/bpi/historical/close.json');
%data = jsondecode(bc);
load bitcoindata
v = struct2cell(data.bpi);
v = cat(1,v{:});
plot(v,'-o')

%bc = webread('https://api.coindesk.com/v1/bpi/historical/close.json');
%data = jsondecode(bc);
load bitcoindata
v = struct2cell(data.bpi);
v = cat(1,v{:});
plot(v,'-ko')
for i = 4:31
    z(i) = (v(i) + v(i-1) + v(i-2) + v(i-3)) / 4;
end
z(1:3) = NaN;  % not a number
hold on, plot(z,'-o')

%bc = webread('https://api.coindesk.com/v1/bpi/historical/close.json');
%data = jsondecode(bc);
load bitcoindata
v = struct2cell(data.bpi);
v = cat(1,v{:});
plot(v,'-ko')
w = [4 3 2 1];
for i = 4:31
    z(i) = (w(1)*v(i) + w(2)*v(i-1) + w(3)*v(i-2) + w(4)*v(i-3)) / sum(w);
end
z(1:3) = NaN;  % not a number
hold on, plot(z,'-o')
